title: "Admin Factions — Cuento Docs"
---

      <div class="docs-eyebrow">Admin Panel</div>
      <h1 class="docs-title">Factions</h1>
      <p class="docs-lead">
        The Factions page lets you build a hierarchy of groups that characters can belong to —
        houses, guilds, factions, species, or any other category your world requires.
        Factions can be nested to any depth using parent–child relationships.
      </p>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-factions.png" alt="Admin Factions page screenshot" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Structure</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Factions form a tree. Top-level factions have a <strong>Level</strong> of <code>0</code>
        and no Parent ID. Child factions have a positive level and a Parent ID pointing to their
        parent. The indentation on the page reflects the nesting depth.
      </p>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Fields</h2>

      <div class="field-list">

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Name</div>
            <div class="field-values">text</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            The display name of the faction, shown on character profiles, the faction list, and anywhere factions are referenced.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Level</div>
            <div class="field-values">number</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            The depth of this faction in the hierarchy. <code>0</code> = top-level; <code>1</code> = one level down, and so on.
            This is set automatically when you use <strong>Add Child</strong> and does not normally need to be edited manually.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Description</div>
            <div class="field-values">text</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            An optional description of the faction, visible to members on the faction's page.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Icon</div>
            <div class="field-values">text</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            An optional icon identifier or image URL displayed alongside the faction name.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Parent ID</div>
            <div class="field-values">number</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            The ID of this faction's parent. Leave empty for a top-level faction. You can find a
            faction's ID in its URL or by noting its position on this page. Changing this value
            moves the faction (and all its children) to a different parent.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Show on profile</div>
            <div class="field-values">checkbox</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            When checked, this faction is displayed on the character profiles of members who belong to it.
            Uncheck to use the faction for internal organisation without surfacing it to players.
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Actions</h2>

      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Save</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Saves changes to that faction's fields. Each faction has its own Save button.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Add Child</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Creates a new faction as a direct child of this one. The child's Level and Parent ID
            are pre-filled automatically. Fill in the remaining fields and click Save on the new row.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
